            <p>Automatically Tracking Internet Protocol (IP) addresses is one method of automatically collecting information about your activities online and information volunteered by you. An IP address is a number that is automatically assigned to your device whenever you surf the internet. Further, we may utilize web beacons, pixel tags, cookies (including third-party cookies), embedded links, and other commonly used information-gathering tools. We may also collect device identifiers.</p>
